WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:05.120
The biggest gap that I see is where organizations,

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:08.880
they are mistaking this work that they're doing

00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:10.440
for actual output.

00:00:10.440 --> 00:00:13.000
So at the board level, we have all of these kind of,

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.640
we're investing in AI initiatives,

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:17.080
but when you think about the ground floor

00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:18.799
and where we're actually working,

00:00:18.799 --> 00:00:20.840
there's a lot of fragmentation still,

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:22.799
and data scientists and analysts

00:00:22.799 --> 00:00:24.740
are working with different tools.

00:00:24.740 --> 00:00:28.160
And until an organization is employing data science

00:00:28.200 --> 00:00:30.600
to the level where they can actually

00:00:30.600 --> 00:00:32.560
base their business decisions on,

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:33.759
they'll always kind of be stuck

00:00:33.759 --> 00:00:35.480
in this experimentation phase.

00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:37.599
And so that's the biggest gap I think organizations

00:00:37.599 --> 00:00:39.040
need to think about.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.880
They're delivering really good value

00:00:40.880 --> 00:00:43.520
in terms of speeding up your productivity,

00:00:43.520 --> 00:00:45.520
being able to automatically code,

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:47.320
being able to generate things

00:00:47.320 --> 00:00:49.959
that have a lot of that high frequency.

00:00:49.959 --> 00:00:53.200
And when you start thinking about agents,

00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:56.220
it's not so much, can an agent do this?

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:58.580
Where it falls apart is fitting that

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:00.099
into your actual environment.

00:01:00.099 --> 00:01:01.900
So thinking about your governance,

00:01:01.900 --> 00:01:03.820
the different tools that you're working with,

00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:06.660
your whole environment as an organization.

00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:09.059
Can your agents actually adapt

00:01:09.059 --> 00:01:11.379
to your organization's environment?

00:01:11.379 --> 00:01:13.300
And so that's the biggest part

00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:14.860
where I feel like they fail.

00:01:14.860 --> 00:01:17.260
The organizations that are really successful with that

00:01:17.260 --> 00:01:19.180
are treating it more like a spectrum

00:01:19.180 --> 00:01:22.260
rather than this kind of binary automate everything

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:24.320
or just do manual processes.

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:26.000
So they're really looking at it

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.120
from two different decisions.

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:29.839
One, do I have this process

00:01:29.839 --> 00:01:32.459
that has high frequency and low risk?

00:01:32.459 --> 00:01:34.120
Yes, let's automate this.

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:35.599
Do we have this other process

00:01:35.599 --> 00:01:39.239
that might be more ambiguous in terms of the result

00:01:39.239 --> 00:01:42.900
and also has a lot of risk involved in that?

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:44.919
That's where you still want that human in the loop.

00:01:44.919 --> 00:01:47.760
And so we're not looking at everything

00:01:47.760 --> 00:01:50.360
as automate everything, throw it in there,

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:52.440
or we're doing everything by hand.

00:01:52.440 --> 00:01:54.760
We really have to look at it from a spectrum.

00:01:54.760 --> 00:01:55.599
Yeah.

00:01:56.480 --> 00:02:00.480
It's not seeing your data science and AI organizations

00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:03.580
as kind of like this experimentation kitchen.

00:02:03.580 --> 00:02:06.839
It's really embracing AI and data

00:02:06.839 --> 00:02:10.399
as an organizational product,

00:02:10.399 --> 00:02:12.740
embedding that into your workflows

00:02:12.740 --> 00:02:15.800
and essentially making that a repeatable process.

00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:17.880
It might be one thing to take a model

00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:19.860
and be able to put it into production,

00:02:19.860 --> 00:02:21.080
but how easy is it for you

00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.600
to take more of your data science workflows

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:26.759
and spread that across the organization and really scale?

00:02:26.759 --> 00:02:29.559
And unless those organizations are really looking at it

00:02:29.559 --> 00:02:31.360
from a holistic view,

00:02:31.360 --> 00:02:34.600
you're always going to be stuck in experimenting,

00:02:34.600 --> 00:02:36.759
prototyping, and not really getting things

00:02:36.759 --> 00:02:38.300
to that production level.

